The defendant George J Key was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant George J Key in court with attorney Gregory A. Renden.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy court clerk: LMS. 

The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.
On motion of the state, the court amended the charge to Theft-Movable Property, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.20(1)(a), a class A misdemeanor.   Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction to the amended charge.

Court sentenced defendant to serve 3 DAYS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for 3 days served; TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges, including DNA surcharge by 10/20/2015 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.   Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit Form.

Defendant George J Key in court with attorney Gregory A Renden.  Michael Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
The parties have agreed to a deferred judgment agreement.The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, pled GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionaire/Wiaver of Rights and Addendum to Plea Questionaire received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgement of Conviction.  The Court reviewed the Intake Requirement and Further Conditions with the defendant.  The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and ordered the proceedings suspended for a period of six months.  Review Hearing scheduled for a later date before Judge Ellen Brostrom, Branch 06, Room 310 in the Safety Building.  Clerk in Branch 06 contacted for Review Hearing Date.  Review hearing scheduled for 07-14-2014 at 08:30 am.
